**Notes**

LPOP temps 2
- Remove the first 2 elements

RPOP
- Remove the last 2 elements

LPUSH temps 24
- Push value 24 at start of list

RPUSH temps 24
- Push value 24 at the end of list

LLEN temps
- Return length of temps list

LINDEX temps 2
- Return temps[2]

LSET temps 2 32
- temps[32] = 2

LTRIM temps 2 5
- temps = temps[2->5] (including 5)

LRANGE temps 2 5
- return temps[2->5]

LPOS temps 25 [RANK 2] [COUNT 3 -> get first 3 indexes] [MAXLEN 10 -> only search 10 elements]
- return index, temps[index]  == 25

LINSERT temps BEFORE 25 15
- Insert value 15 before value 25

LREM temps [0 1 -2] 25
- -2 means from right to left remove 2 values of 25
- 0 means remove all 25
- 1 means from left to right remove 1 value of 25
